{
  "texts": [
    "AI advancement, however, continues in this direction.",
    "Calls for stopping the technological progress have not been effective.",
    "Relatively early in development of social actor AI, computer science researchers created benchmarks for human likeness to enable people to create more humanlike AI (Kahn et al., 2007).",
    "That human likeness has increased since.",
    "Our proposal has less to do with regulating how advanced or how humanlike AI becomes, and more to do with regulating how AI impacts the psychology of users by providing a model for prosocial behavior or by ignoring, confronting, or rectifying antisocial behavior."
  ]
}